16
00:01:01,470 --> 00:01:05,610
Anyone with a link will be able to visit your site from their browser.

17
00:01:05,610 --> 00:01:10,470
We would consider this type of environment a production environment.

18
00:01:10,740 --> 00:01:15,150
Production environments are great for hosting a site, but not for development.

19
00:01:15,150 --> 00:01:16,980
They're not easy to update.

20
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:19,440
Let's say a template needs to be updated.

21
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:22,620
Files must be uploaded manually to a server.

22
00:01:22,620 --> 00:01:24,720
This process can take a while.

23
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:29,400
Also, updating a live site can disrupt a user's experience.

24
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:34,320
If you accidentally upload a broken file, visitors may receive errors.

25
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:39,570
Production environment should have the most stable copy of your WordPress site.

26
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:46,220
As developers, we need an environment that allows us to make as many breaking changes as possible.

27
00:01:46,230 --> 00:01:49,710
This is referred to as a development environment.

28
00:01:49,740 --> 00:01:54,240
Unlike a production environment, the development environments are private.

29
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:56,370
They're only accessible to us.

30
00:01:56,370 --> 00:02:00,780
If we break a site that's perfectly fine, users won't notice.

31
